tweet: This administration continues to institute new regulations on energy production and place new restrictions on pipelines that handcuff America’s energy industry.   We need to unleash domestic energy production!

name: Robert Sprague
tweet: It wasn’t all that long ago that America was energy independent, we can get there again.   Ohio should be a leader in restoring America to energy independence; we just need Washington DC to get out of the way.

name: Robert Sprague
tweet: Radical anti-energy ideologues like Sarah Bloom Raskin shouldn’t be overseeing America’s financial system.  Americans are seeing the flaws of her agenda every day at the gas pump.  I’m pleased to see her nomination has been withdrawn.

name: Robert Sprague
tweet: The way out of this energy crisis isn’t draining our strategic oil reserves or promoting electric cars.   The solution is embracing the incredible oil and natural gas resources we’re blessed with here in Ohio and unleashing domestic energy production.

name: Robert Sprague
tweet: Rising gas prices are devastating families at the pump, but international unrest isn’t the driving force behind these record price increases.  These prices are the result of bad energy policy from the Biden White House.
